/* Background */ The idea of Hypatia as a victim of a witch-hunt is anachronistic and wrong. The earliest and most reliable account of her murder from her contemporary Socrates Scholasticus mentions nothing about witchcraft and describes her murder as a disastrous result of her entanglement in a political feud between the bishop Cyril and the prefect Orestes. Accusations of witchcraft are only mentioned in sources written hundreds of years later. See the article [[Hypatia]] for further details.
